    <name>Build collective agency in your classroom.</name>
    <intro></intro>
    <introformat>1</introformat>
    <content>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{92173d2c-c0de-417e-9edf-e99a07e6711b}{212}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:10,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;a href="$@PAGEVIEWBYID*9888@$" target="_blank"&gt;Hohn and Rivera (2019)&lt;/a&gt; defined collective efficacy for adult learners to mean&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;when and how&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;the&amp;nbsp;group enhances feelings of power and control to be effective as individuals and as a group.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{92173d2c-c0de-417e-9edf-e99a07e6711b}{215}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:10,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;You can build feelings of collective agency in your classroom by creating class norms.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{92173d2c-c0de-417e-9edf-e99a07e6711b}{218}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:10,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Begin by asking your adult learners to share the conditions that create an ideal learning environment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;in the classroom. Also ask them about the negative things they’ve experienced when interacting in&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;the classroom. Use the positive and negative traits as a framework for creating group ground rules.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;After the class has created a master set of rules, determine the rules you feel are best. Post the rules&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;at the front of the class and review them throughout the semester to ensure they’re effective and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@3F3F3F,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;applicable to the learning environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;​Go back to the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="$@COURSEVIEWBYID*294@$#section-5" target="_blank"&gt;Try It Yourself Section&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;for a list of all Try it Yourself Options.&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{92173d2c-c0de-417e-9edf-e99a07e6711b}{221}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:10,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/divider%20wave.png" alt="" width="1920" height="195" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
